{
    "identity": "nprot-108",
    "title": "Immunostaining of DDR proteins in senescent cells",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Introduction",
            "content": "We present here a brief yet detailed methodology to study the activation of a number of DNA damage response factors in senescent human fibroblasts."
        },
        {
            "header": "Reagents",
            "content": "poly-D-lysine \\(SIGMA P6407 5 mg)\r\n\n\nMethanol/Aceton 1:1\r\n\n\nPBG 10x stock solution: 5% BSA, 2% of gelatin from cold water fish skin \\(SIGMA cat. G-7765) in PBS 1x\r\n\n\nAntibodies:\r\n\n\n&#x3B3;H2AX mouse Upstate Biotechnology \\(cat.05-636) 1:200\r\n\n\nATMpS1981 rabbit Rockland \\(cat. 600-401-400) 1:300\r\n\n\npS/TQ rabbit Cell Signaling Technology \\(cat. #2851)1:100\r\n\n\nSMC1pS996 rabbit Bethyl Laboratories \\(cat. A300-050A) 1:500\r\n\n\nDAPI \\(SIGMA cat.D-9564)\r\n\n\nMowiol mounting medium \\(CALBIOCHEM  cat. 475904)"
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "1) Prepare poly-D-lysinated coverslips \\(poly D lysine 50\u03bcg/ml)\r\n\n\n2) Plate 15-20 x 10\n3\ncells on coverslips 1 day before the staining\r\n\n\n3) Wash cells gently 2x5\u2019in PBS1x\r\n\n\n4) Fix and permeabilize cells for 2\u2019 with methanol/aceton 1:1 at RT\r\n\n\n5) Block cells for 30\u2019 with PBG1x\r\n\n\n6) Stain with primary antibodies diluted in PBG1x at indicated concentration for 1h at RT in a humidified chamber\r\n\n\n7) Wash cells gently 3x5\u2019in PBG1x\r\n\n\n8) Stain with secondary antibodies diluted in PBG1x for 1h at RT in a dark humidified chamber\r\n\n\n9) Wash cells gently 2x5\u2019 in PBG1x and 2x5\u2019in PBS1x\r\n\n\n10) Stain with Dapi for 5\u2019 in the dark\r\n\n\n11) Mount coverslips with 3\u03bcl of Mowiol mounting medium\r\n\n\n12) Let the coverslips dry before microscope analysis"
        },
        {
            "header": "Timing",
            "content": "4 h"
        },
        {
            "header": "Critical Steps",
            "content": "Use always a positive \\(X-Rays treated cells 2-5 Gy) and a negative control \\(proliferating or even better contact inhibited \\(for a short period) quiescient cells) to reduce background"
        },
        {
            "header": "Troubleshooting",
            "content": "Using different type of fixative can allow better staining depending on antibody\r\n\n\nLipofuscin accumulation in senescent cells can give an high citosolic autofluorescent background material"
        },
        {
            "header": "References",
            "content": "d'Adda di Fagagna _et al._ A DNA damage checkpoint response in telomere-initiated senescence _Nature_ **426**, 194-198 \\(2003)"
        }
    ],
